<TITLE> War crimes trial soon: Ashraf </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Apr 9(bdnews24.com)- Local government minister Syed Ashraful Islam said Friday that the trial of war criminals will begin soon after investigations. Syed Ashraf, spokesperson of the ruling Awami League, was addressing a public rally on Friday at Pallabi Bus Stand in Mirpur, Dhaka. The rallly was organised to raise public opinion in support of the trial of war criminals. Syed Ashraf said, "War criminals possess thousands of crores of taka and have strong link at home and abroad." "They will conspire to hinder the trial process but no one will be able to resist us if we remain united and determined," he said. "Trial of war criminals is an electoral pledge of the government," he said adding that appointments of investigation officials, prosecutors' panel and tribunal have already been completed. "Investigation is underway," he said adding that the trial would begin soon after the investigation was over. Referring to the opposition, Ashraf said, "They urge the government to generate electricity instead of trying the war criminals but they did not generate a single watt of electricity while in power." "Khaleda regime has given the nation khambas (electric poles) in the name of power generation. They plundered thousands of crores of taka," he alleged. The rally chaired by Awami League's Pallabi unit chief Ilias Uddin Mollah was attended among others by Awami League city secretary Mofazzal Hossain Maya and vice-president Mukul Chowdhury. bdne
